  <p align="justify">Diatoms are marine organisms with an ornate silica shell. This silica from ancient deposits of dead diatoms is useful in everyday life in products such as diatomaceous earth and toothpaste.</p>
  <p align="justify">Diatoms are traditionally divided into two broad catagories: 
  <b>centric</b> diatoms (Centrales), which are radially symmetric, and <b>pennate</b> diatoms (Pennales), 
